"footnoteSeqID";"Footnote"
"1";"During the 2010 Census, the relationship between the members of the household was determined on the basis of a set of questions completed for all members of the household, differently from the 2000 Census. In the 2000 Census, the reference person was used to establish the relationship between the members of the household. In 2010 however, enumerators were instructed to choose a reference person as a mere helpful tool in finding the person who could be most helpful in completing the housing form, given that the owner of the living quarter or the one responsible for paying the rent is often the one who knows the most of the living quarter. Relationship to head of household was not asked in the 2010 Census."
"2";"These data have been randomly rounded to protect confidentiality. Individual figures may not add up to totals, and values for the same data may vary in different tables."
"3";"Data refer to other reference member aged 0-14 years."
"4";"422240 households categorised as  "Visitor only" or "Not classifiable " are excluded from this table as a "Household reference person" is not identified in "Visitor only " and "Not classifiable" households."
"5";"1 034 818 persons in households categorised as  "Visitor only" or "Not classifiable " are excluded from this table as a "Household reference person" is not identified in "Visitor only " and "Not classifiable" households."
"6";"Includes households with "adult children with live-in parents" which is a type of household where the child is head of the household and in many cases, the parent is a dependent of the child."
"7";"Data exclude institutional households and other households."
"8";"Data refer to population 15 years of age or more."
"9";"Bermuda is 100 per cent urban."
"10";"Data includes a single family nucleus and other persons."
"11";"Excludes households for which there is no data."
"12";"Includes one or more family nuclei."
"13";"The unknown category includes not stated values and/or persons/households for which there is no data."
"14";"Excluding the institutional population."
"15";"Data refer to persons who are living together."
"16";"In the Brazilian Census 2010, the families (or family nuclei) were not identified by the interviewer, but through a derived methodology."
"17";"Data refer to population 10 years of age or more."
"18";"The types of households, which are related to the concepts of families, were derived for the housing units in non-indigenous census tracts."
"19";"Source: Brazilian Demographic Census 2010, Sample Survey. The sampling rate depends on the number of persons in the county, according to the estimates of population. The total sampling rate is approximately 11% of the total households."
"20";"The classification of the marital status is the result of a cross-tabulation of two questions, one about de facto marital status (living, not living, never lived with a partner) and the other one about the legal marital status (single, married, divorced, widowed)."
"21";"Including polygamous families."
"22";"Source: Statistics Canada, 2016 Census of Population - 25% Sample Data."
"23";"To ensure confidentiality, the values, including totals are randomly rounded either up or down to a multiple of '5' or '10.' As a result, when these data are summed or grouped, the total value may not match the individual values since totals and sub-totals are independently rounded. Similarly, percentages, which are calculated on rounded data, may not necessarily add up to 100%."
"24";"'Marital status' refers to whether or not a person is living in a common-law union as well as the legal marital status of those who are not living in a common-law union. All persons aged less than 15 are considered as never married and not living common law."
"25";"Because of rounding, totals are not in all cases the sum of the respective components."
"26";"Based on a 20 per cent sample of census returns."
"27";"Including same sex marriages."
"28";"Data are estimates from sample enquiry."
"29";""Nuclear household" refers to "One unextended nuclear family"."
"30";""Non-nuclear household" refers to "Related persons forming no nuclear family" and "Unrelated persons only"."
"31";""Unknown" refers to a vertically extended nuclear family, a horizontally extended nuclear family and two or more nuclear families."
"32";"Includes married and consensually married."
"33";"Data include separated."
"34";"Includes two or more family nuclei."
"35";"Data refer to private households only."
"36";"Refers to households with a head of household only."
"37";"Excludes persons living in collective households that do not present a head of household."
"38";"Data refer to government controlled areas."
"39";"Including category "Married but separated"."
"40";"Data refer to registered partnerships."
"41";"Data refer to households comprised of couples with children less than 26 years of age and not economically active."
"42";"The head of household is married or in a union."
"43";"The head of household is separated from marriage or consensual union."
"44";"Includes persons in consensual unions and persons separated from such unions."
"45";"Excludes nomadic Indian tribes."
"46";"Data for certain cells suppressed by national statistical office for confidentiality reasons."
"47";"Includes data for the Indian-held part of Jammu and Kashmir, the final status of which has not yet been determined."
"48";"Excluding Mao-Maram, Paomata and Purul sub-divisions of Senapati district of Manipur."
"49";"The household reference person is the first person listed on the household’s member list, either a member of a couple or another household member age 15 or over (when no couple is present), and is not necessarily the head of household."
"50";"Includes data for East Jerusalem and Israeli residents in certain other territories under occupation by Israeli military forces since June 1967."
"51";"Based on a 17 per cent sample of census returns."
"52";"Refer to households in which it was not possible to identify the 'head' of household."
"53";"Excluding diplomatic personnel outside the country and foreign military and civilian personnel and their dependants stationed in the area."
"54";"Includes persons not related to head of household and children already married."
"55";"Data refer to multi-person households."
"56";"Excludes the islands of St. Brandon and Agalega."
"57";"A household is defined as the group of persons inside a private housing unit."
"58";"Includes unknown and consensually married persons."
"59";"Includes only households with a head of household age 12 years or older."
"60";"Category 'Divorced and not remarried' includes 'Married but separated'."
"61";"Excludes non-residents present in country at time of census (visitors, foreigners temporarily residing in country, etc.)."
"62";"Tiraspol, Bender, Slobozia, Ribnita, Camenca  Yrigoricpol/Grigoriopol are districts from Transnistria where the census was not conducted."

"68";"Data refer to resident population which comprises Singapore citizens and permanent residents."

"70";"Data contain households with economically inactive children under age 28, and households with children aged 28 and over, economically active, living with lone parents."

"74";"Data include couples in consensual unions."

"76";"Data includes same sex civil partnerships."
